{
  "texts": [
    "However, a notable portion of these datasets is marked by characteristics such as noise and sparsity.",
    "This poses a substantial challenge when it comes to accurately identifying biological features, especially during the integration of various omics data sources (Joyce and Palsson, 2006).",
    "The challenge of imbalanced datasets, where sample sizes vary across categories, is pervasive in ML.",
    "Researchers address this through resampling strategies such as oversampling and undersampling (Maimon and Rokach, 2005).",
    "For instance, Li et al. (2021) employed the synthetic minority oversampling technique (SMOTE) to bolster the representation of minority cases, a crucial step in the identification of effector proteins."
  ]
}